sequenceDiagram
    title x402 Payment Flow: Standard vs. Hardened
    
    participant Agent as AI Agent
    participant Server as 402 Payment Server
    participant Middleware as HardenedX402Client
    participant Facilitator as Facilitator API (Base L2)
    participant Chain as On-Chain Settlement
    
    Note over Agent,Chain: 🔴 STANDARD FLOW (Vulnerable)
    Agent->>Server: GET /resource
    Server-->>Agent: 402 Payment Required + spec
    Agent->>Agent: Sign EIP-712 token with<br/>resource_url, description, reason
    Agent->>Server: Retry with X-Payment header<br/>⚠️ PII in plaintext
    Server->>Facilitator: Forward payment token<br/>⚠️ PII in plaintext
    Facilitator->>Chain: Settle USDC transfer
    Chain-->>Facilitator: On-chain receipt
    Facilitator-->>Server: Confirmation
    Server-->>Agent: Serve resource
    
    Note over Agent,Chain: 🟢 HARDENED FLOW (Presidio)
    Agent->>Server: GET /resource
    Server-->>Agent: 402 Payment Required + spec
    Agent->>Middleware: Construct payment token
    Middleware->>Middleware: 1️⃣ PIIFilter: Scan & redact PII
    Middleware->>Middleware: 2️⃣ PolicyEngine: Check spending limits
    Middleware->>Middleware: 3️⃣ ReplayGuard: Check for duplicates
    Middleware->>Middleware: 4️⃣ AuditLog: Emit structured event
    alt All controls pass
        Middleware->>Server: Retry with REDACTED X-Payment header
        Server->>Facilitator: Forward redacted token
        Facilitator->>Chain: Settle USDC transfer
        Chain-->>Facilitator: Receipt
        Facilitator-->>Server: Confirmation
        Server-->>Agent: Serve resource
    else Control fails
        Middleware-->>Agent: Raise exception<br/>(PolicyViolation/ReplayDetected)
        Agent->>Agent: Handle error / retry logic
    end
    
    Note right of Middleware: ✅ PII never leaves trust boundary unredacted<br/>✅ Spending enforced pre-execution<br/>✅ Replay attacks blocked<br/>✅ Audit trail for compliance
